04/05/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Foreign Minister Razvan Ungureanu left for the United States on Tuesday (3 May) to discuss what his office described as measures that would give a "fresh impetus to strategic relations" between the two countries. He is due to meet with Secretary of State Condoleezza Rice, her two predecessors Colin Powell and Madeleine Albright, and UN Secretary General Kofi Annan. 
In other news, the Romanian government has decided to set up a special task force to co-ordinate efforts by several agencies against tax evasion, contraband and illegal employment. (AFP, AP - 03/05/05)
